Anne, Ritz Cove is next to the Ritz Cartlon, of Dana Point. I do not live in Ritz Cove, but near by. Clearly I won't give out where. Trust me, the food is devine. The service is pompous, the marble floor gross, but that is the Ritz.<br><br>
The place is crawling with arab types with surfettes hanging on their arms, but we are in a banquet room. This is the, no I won't say, but it involves many local mayors and congressfolks, and they don't mind my lap top at all, there are actually quite a few here.  Hope mine is wine proof. God knows it is WHINE proof.<br><br>
ha ha.
